author: WSJ Staff
title: Ryan and Trump: A Tense Partnership From the Start
text:
House Speaker Paul Ryan, who on Wednesday announced that he won’t seek re-election in November, has had an uneasy relationship with President Donald Trump since the early days of Mr. Trump’s campaign Here are some of the tensions, differences—and occasional agreements—in their own words.
Dec. 8, 2015
